flag provided but not defined: -load
Usage of ./app:
  -add string
    	Add a new user and create their personal database (usage: --add username)
  -add-cluster string
    	Deprecated: cluster peers are configured via CLUSTER_PEERS in .env
  -clear
    	Use with --import to clear current runtime data before import
  -clearruntimes
    	Clear old runtime folders
  -config-http string
    	Configure HTTP service (usage: --config-http enabled=true port=9090 host=0.0.0.0 tls=false)
  -config-tcp string
    	Configure TCP service (usage: --config-tcp enabled=true port=5000 host=0.0.0.0)
  -config-ws string
    	Configure WebSocket service (usage: --config-ws enabled=true port=8080 host=0.0.0.0). Client controls polling interval.
  -export
    	Export database and exit (usage: --export [dbname])
  -exportlastruntime
    	Export database from last runtime folder and exit
  -flushtokens
    	Flush all authentication tokens and exit
  -import string
    	Import database from file
  -importpersistent
    	Load database from persistent backup and start server
  -lastruntime
    	Load database from last runtime folder and start server
  -list-cluster
    	List cluster peers from CLUSTER_PEERS and exit
  -list-services
    	List service configurations and exit
  -listusers
    	List all users and exit
  -password string
    	Password for user (if not provided, a random one will be generated)
  -peer-metrics
    	Show peer metrics (usage: --peer-metrics [peer_address])
  -remove string
    	Remove a user and delete their personal database (usage: --remove username)
  -remove-cluster string
    	Deprecated: cluster peers are configured via CLUSTER_PEERS in .env
